<H3> <TI>   Official Hints at Compromises in U.S. Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2512041493 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 25 Dec 
93 Morning Edition -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2512041493 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Received via Nikkei Telecom database] </F>
  [Text] On 24 December, a senior Foreign Ministry official 
pointed out that "fundamentally, the United States will be 
making demands on Japan at the Japanese-U.S. framework talks 
because Japan has a huge trade surplus with the United States." 
At the same time, he hinted at the possibility that Japan may 
make more compromises than the United States, saying, "It is 
necessary for Japan to make further compromises (to reach 
agreement at the framework talks)." 

</TEXT>

