<F P=102>  OW2512054393 Naha OKINAWA TIMES in Japanese 23 Dec 93 
Morning Edition p 2--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2512054393 </F>
<F P=104>  Naha OKINAWA TIMES </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Concerning the recent accident involving aircraft 
belonging to the U.S. Marine Corps, the prefectural government 
asked an office of the four military branches coordinator of the 
U.S. Forces on Okinawa on 22 December to investigate the cause 
of the accident and to prevent similar accidents from recurring. 
The prefectural government pointed out that although the 
accident occurred in training airspace, concerns of local 
residents who live near Kadena Air Base [KAB] are growing 
because the aircraft took off from KAB. Accordingly, the office 
was asked to conduct a through safety review. 

