<H3> <TI>   Security Official Urges Corruption Papers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2312182193 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1439 GMT 23 Dec 
93 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2312182193 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, December 23 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The 
papers relating to the bribery by some members of the parliament 
and the government will be destructed soon. It is necessary to 
take steps for protection [to protect] them against destruction. 
This was told to journalists by head of the department in the 
general board on ensuring state security L. Sanjaasuren [name as 
received]. He pleaded the reliable sources informing about the 
possible destruction of the important papers being made ready. 
  The documents were preserved by the former head of the State 
security organs J. Baatar who was relieved of this office the 
other day. L. Sanjaasuren demanded to deliver them copies of 
the papers, preserve all the information kept in the memory of 
the computers in this respect and to cease temporarily any staff 
shifts in this office. 
  L. Sanjaasuren stressed the significance of forming a 
service 
for struggle with corruption. 
  Ensuring guarantees for not imposing punishment on those who 
was forced to give bribes. 
  We are planning measures to be implemented lest this demand 
is accepted, L. Sanjaasuren said. 

</TEXT>

