<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. Criticized on Policy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2312061793 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 23 Dec 
93 Morning Edition -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2312061793 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Received via Nikkei Telecom Database] </F>
  [Text] Commenting on reports that the United States 
declared in the Japan-U.S. comphrensive economic talks that it 
is not seeking to set numerical targets, a Foreign Ministry 
source on 22 December criticized the United States, saying "the 
United States is calling on Japan to raise foreign products' 
market shares in Japan to the level of their shares in the seven 
industrialized nations (G-7). That is as bad as setting 
numerical targets." 
  The source added that "it was decided in July (at the time 
of 
Japan and the United States agreeing on frameworks) that no 
numerical targets should be set." 

</TEXT>

